 :avatar: n. Syn. 1. Among people working on virtual reality and {cyberspace}
interface, an "avatar" is an icon or representation of a user in a shared
virtual reality. The term is sumetimes used on {MUD}s. 2. [CMU, Tektronix]
{root}, {superuser}. There are quite a few Unix machines on which the name of
the superuser account is `avatar' rather than `root'. This quirk was
originated by a CMU hacker who disliked the term `superuser', and was
propagated through an ex-CMU hacker at Tektronix.